	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				***If you wanna learn more about quad kiting, dueling, or soloing, then read this.***<BR>
<BR>
Quad Kiting: Most people I have talked to from &quot;Bluebie&quot; server, don't quad kite til lvl 29 (bonds of force, aoe snare) or never actually realize how to do this. You can't truly quad kite til... say lvl 16 or 20... What you can do is get a sow (I use my jboots which are slower but castable at all times) when you get a sow, make sure you are FM. You don't wanna waste the sow medding. To pull the mobs, they have to be blue con, and not HIGH HIGH blue (you're lvl 23, mobs are all 23... no... maybe 1, but not all). I seriously recommend you pull with Staff of the Temperate Flux. Most, if not all, Wizards use this staff to quad kite (instant right click lower element effect -9svfire and cold, great for duels and PvP) *more info on how to get the no drop quest only staff in http://www.graffe.com/ * Ok anyhow... If you don't have staff, pull with the QUICKEST NUKE you got (low lvl obviously, low mana, low dmg) when ya get 4 mobs, be sure you don't run out of range... Run in one huge circle, this will gather all the mobs together. Run as fast as you freakin can, clicking on the low lvl fast nuke, when it says out of range, wait about 3-6secs to get some distance. When completely sure you have stopped and won't be interrupted, AOE!!! BAM you got all 4 mobs! Ok now run!!!!!! You can keep running straight, or back (making a semi-circle so you do not get hit) keep doing this til they fall. If you see you can't do it, don't waste mana, just zone. A really really smart thing to do (RECOMMENDED BY EVERYONE) is to try your best to get pairs of mobs... For example, pull 2 sarnaks and 2 skeles. The skeles won't run when low on hp, but sarnaks will unless they are with another sarnak. If one of the sarnak dies, the other is low on hp, and the 2 skeles (or 1) is alive, run to get help or just let it be. What I do is get 4 of the same mobs, that way only 1 will run, and that's when everything else is dead. If sow falls... BYE BYE you sure as hell can count on dying. Exp is great, don't try whites, yellows, or reds. Just aim for blues, GREAT EXP!<BR>
<BR>
Dueling and PvPing: Wizards are great at dueling. They are ****ing amazing! I run into some dumbasses out there who don't know wizzys potential, being wizards themselves! Listen, you most likely can't beat a necro, you DEFINETLY CAN beat a mage. Haha epic pet is a bit hard, but you CAN do it. The only classes I say you should worry bout is necro, SK, monk (if epic, they can interrupt the hell out of you no matter how high channeling, but they go down fast when ya get nukes in), and rarely gotta watch out for shamans. (I know you are all wondering why I didn't put druids in... OMG people... you really think a druid can withstand such amount of power??? Get real!) Necros... They are ****ing hard since they can lifetap (which is a *****) and their dots (they die before dots usually...). They are hard to kill til around 40+, the you OWN them. At 50+... eh we'll see... Take out necro first, you can root pet (svmagic low) and stand back and nuke away. SK... I really find it impossible to beat these guys, usually run from them... Being a PvPer and seeing them frequently (not as much, being a Dark Elf) don't fret bout it, just don't duel em. If PvP... you are screwed unless 40+. Like I said 40+ our nukes get incredible. Monks... not much to them. If they got high SVMagic (usually people don't aim for fire and cold resists) then you can't root em. 29+ use yonder to get away and nuke from afar, below use shadow step. Their HP is low but count on them putting up a rough fight, you can beat em. What can I say bout Shamans? They rock on PvP at around lvl 34. They get the malise line of spells (lowers all resists cept disease, count on it going below normal), they get pets, extremely good dots, DECENT nukes, heals for themselves, and some can melee and tank quite a bit. All I can say is take out pet first, then deal with shaman. Shamans can be really rough, they can (and often will) use all their mana just to heal themselves while you waste your own mana nuking. Haha sometimes they can't keep up. Depends on the player, definetly on this class. If player gets 1 malise in, he knows he can kill you. Even I know it. If he tries to nuke or heal etc, he's as good as dead. Now I know you all want me to get into mages, so straight to the point. Don't fret bout it! They aren't hard! Their nukes don't keep up for the lvl, and wizards  aren't called channelers for nothing. You can regain concentration often, but those air pets are a *****. They are made to stun, and they work well. All I can say (which has worked MANY MANY times for me) is root pet, back away, and blast the mage. He'll go down before you. It often happens. Player Killing or Dueling as a Wizard doesn't get fun or easy til... I'd say either lvl 20 or 24. I learn ALOT (you'd be amazed) from all my classes. I can play a lvl 5 char as good as a lvl  50 once I get into it. For ****ing sakes I got 190int being a noob in Tallon Zek (not to the game) and I got more experience than half the people posting here. Take my advice, don't flame for my bragging, it's the truth I'm not insulting anyone by it. Take my advice and use it well!!! Kill some lighties (I favor the darkies, sorry!!!) out there and god damn it, stop worshipping Innoruuk. Solusek Ro gave us our magic and we shouldn't be ashamed of it!!!!!! Love ya all bye bye :-)<BR>
<BR>
Netsuki WildFire<BR>
Wizard of the 24th Season (HAHA and you thought I'd be higher) of Solusek Ro<BR>
Tallon Zek<BR>
<BR>
Netzuki DarkStalker<BR>
Necromancer of the 35th Season (not good enough?) of Innoruuk<BR>
