			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Was reading through the messages and saw posts that spoke of Wizzies not being able to kite. Hmmmmmmm well granted Wizzies are tough to kite and until lvl 29 its single target Root and Nuke providing you have SOW cast on you or use a potion. In the beginning it stinks but life gets REAL good after lvl 29 when you get the Bonds of Force spell. This spell not only allows you to kite but with an AOE nuke spell you can Quad kite. Bonds of Force is like the Druids &quot;Snare spell&quot;. You will need Jboots or carry a bottle of SOW potion to quad kite. Get the following spells up. (1) your absolute cheapest lvl 1 nuke (unless you have a Staff of Temperate Flux which is a mana free pulling tool), (2) your Bonds of Force Spell, (3) your best Area (AOE)Nuke and (4)a medium lvl nuke to finish off the leftovers. PRACTICE! PRACTICE! PRACTICE this in a low lvl zone to get the hang of it. OK heres what I did and still do. Fire up the Jboots or take a swig of sow potion (NOTE: My SOW potions last for 36 minutes . It helps if you have a stopwatch that you start when you cast a SOW potion that way you will know if you have enough time to complete a pull before you slow down)If SOW wears off in the middle of a pull your toast. Using your lvl 1 nuke or Temperate Flux Staff agro up to but not more then 4 mobs (and ONLY 4 or less). When they chase you run in big circles around them to get them in a nice tight group, external view is helpful so you can look behind you and will help to tell if they are grouped tight enough, about three circles around them should do. After you have them in a tight group run away from them paying special care NOT to run in a direction that will  agro further mobs. When you get to a safe distance (only practice will tell you what that is)cast your Bonds of Force spell on them. It will snare all of them in one cast as it is an AOE spell. Be careful NOT to cast Bonds of Force if the mobs are close to you or it will snare you too. Then run a bit stop  Nukem with the AOE spell run again and so on. After a few AOE nukes either they all die together or one of them is just a little tougher and stands alone when the other 3 are dead. Finish him with the Medium Nuke. It gets better when you get Atols Spectral Shakles at lvl 51 and the AOE spells get more efficient. I've started this process at lvl 29 and since finding groups for a wiz can be tough (as you all know)I have been solo  90% of the time. I'm now lvl 57 and quad kite in Skyfire. Hope this helps someone. Good Luck! 
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
