			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I found this post on eq.castesrealm.com as I thought it was a great startagy from lvl 25-29.<BR>
--------------------<BR>
--------------------<BR>
<BR>
It was in the Sarnak Fort in Lake of Ill Omen that I became completely fed up with the people pulling. I either waited for an eternity for our warrior to get all buffed up only to have it wear off by the time we actually pulled a group of mobs that gave a decent amount of experience, or had the ranger who couldn't help but pull that Sarnak Revenant and his four recruit buddies. So I asked for a parting sow and disbanded. <BR>
As I walked out of the fort, 2 sarnaks popped from their gaurd positions in front of the entrance. They chased me accross the field as I kited one of them with Frost Shock. I accidentally hit the wrong macro and cast Column of Lightning, and to my surprise, both sarnaks were hit for 120+ pts. I continued this and the original sarnak died, leaving the other sarnak less than half health (no mana). Had a group finish him off, and got the exp. <BR>
More to the point, the tower overlooking the 'backdoor' area is usually inhabited by 3-4 sarnaks, and barely camped. I found that If I could get a sow, I could cast leatherskin, take a couple hits to pull all of them, and run them down the valley just north of FM zone hitting with the CoL spell for a full bar of mana, and dropping all 4. at 25-29 this equated to approx. 1/5-1/4 bub of exp. <BR>
<BR>
Warning: this is not safe, many things can mess this up. It is completely dependant upon the SoW. But if you can get it to work, it's the best way to get exp. I went from 25-29 in 4 days.<BR>
<BR>
--------------------<BR>
--------------------<BR>
<BR>
But what I dont quite understand is how this wizard kited the sarnaks as you dont get bonds of force (area effect snare) untill level 29...<BR>
Was it the Frost Shock thats slowed down the sarnak because everyone knows if a sarnak is running at u doing 50 dmg/hit you dont have much time to cast a spell if you want to live.<BR>
<BR>
Naldyyen <BR>
